CANBERRA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Australia will provide transport
for relief supplies and a mobile hospital to Papua New Guinea
(PNG) following Friday's tsunami tragedy.The disaster center said late Saturday that hundreds are missing
and thousands are without food and shelter.Robert Igara, the government's chief secretary, said the
population in the area affected by the tsunami was 8,000 to 10,000
people.Foreign Affairs Minister Alexander Downer said a Royal
Australian Air Force C-130 Hercules aircraft now in Papua New
Guinea on training exercises would be diverted to deliver relief
supplies.